description: She’s bold, she’s beautiful, and she’s your best hope of escaping the raptors nipping at your heels. She’s Shanna, the She Devil! That’s right, fanboys – the wait is finally over: Award-winning creator Frank Cho brings you Marvel’s bodacious jungle girl as you’ve never seen her before: Reborn from Nazi science gone mad to battle her genetic destiny on an island full of prehistoric horrors. Trust us, Shanna has never looked this good…or acted this bad.
name: The Killing Season: Part One

description: Shanna has never looked this good…or acted this bad. In issue #2, raptors become the least of the Doc and his crew’s problems when Shanna begins to roam the camp and create shockwaves of her own.
name: The Killing Season: Chapter Two

description: What could be worse than a dozen hungry raptors? How about the guy who tops the neighborhood food chain? Doc and his crew race across the Savage Land – and straight into the drooling jaws of a ravenous T-Rex. Can Shanna save them?
name: The Killing Season: Part Three

description: Having survived their experience with the hungry T-Rex – thanks to Shanna -- Doc and his crew scour a labyrinthine Nazi lab in search of an antidote to the plague that’s ravaging their camp. What they find, however, is something much more. And nothing can prepare them for what’s waiting outside.
name: The Killing Season: Part Four

description: Things just got a lot worse for our feisty heroine. It's a feeding frenzy in the jungle as thousands and thousands of razor-toothed raptors cut a bloody swathe through anything and everything in their path. They've just made a T-Rex their supper - will Shanna be their dessert?
name: The Killing Season: Part Five

description: It's eye-popping action from cover-to-cover as Shanna stumbles into the middle of a mass migration of razor-toothed raptors, each of which would love to make her an afternoon snack, and has to slice her way to freedom!
name: The Killing Season: Part Six

description: It’s the climactic conclusion of Award-Winning creator Frank Cho’s dinosaur epic. Up to her…er…ears in raptors that want to make her their main course, Shanna must make a fatal gamble.
name: The Killing Season: Part Seven

description:
First you laugh, then you'll cry. Laugh along with Agent X as he cuts off his enemy's hands,  twice! Then cry for our hero as he sinks a boatload of his own money.    
 
Alex caught the invisible man... but what to do with him now?
name: Hold That Ghost, Part 2

description: What will Agent X do when he's hired to kill a man who wants to die but can't be killed? And why's that funny? Comics' funniest writer Evan Dorkin tells you why!
name: If At First You Don't Succeed, Die, Die Again

description: Agent X teams up with his target to defend the honor of a few hot girls, and laughter ensues! This thought-provoking tale explores laughter, fights, and witty dialogue by acclaimed award-winner Evan Dorkin!
name: Fight the Power!

description: Christine and her father are reunited at long last. But will Alex and Dante stick around for the family reunion?
name: Out With A Bang

description: He's BACK, and you won't BELIEVE who he's brought with him! The Mighty Marvel Merc with no memory returns! And so does GAIL SIMONE, UDON and ... (wait for it) ... DEADPOOL?!?!? The 3-part AGENT X series finale you never expected starts here, and you won't believe where it leads...
name: Deadpool Walkin', Part 1: Our Lives in Fracture

description: Last issue's shocking return of Deadpool raised more questions than answers... So who better to figure it all out than the creative team that changed DEADPOOL into AGENT X in the first place?!?
name: Deadpool Walkin', Part 2: Foul Brain Stew

description:
FINAL ISSUE! It's the end of the road for AGENT X (yeah, we know ... but for real this time) ... but could that ending mean a new beginning for the long-lost merc known as Deadpool? And what will be the final fate of the man named Alex Hayden?

Deadpool's back! And Black Swan takes advantage of both Alex and Deadpool being togheter, and telepathically absorbs their powers.
name: Deadpool Walkin', Part 3: A Means to an End

description: "HEROES AND VILLIANS" PART 1 (OF 4) Brand-new story arc! The Brotherhood of Mutants is back with Nocturne from the Exiles, and a surprise shocker of a member!
name: Heroes and Villains

name: Treachery

name: Foreshadowing

first_appearance_locations.name: Jean Grey School for Higher Learning

location_credits.name: Jean Grey School for Higher Learning

description: "HEROES AND VILLAINS" PART 4 (OF 4) The explosive conclusion to the battle between the X-Men and the newly re-formed Brotherhood of Mutants! When the dust clears, will everyone remain standing
name: Full Circle

description: Chris Claremont & Salvador Larroca bring you a self-contained holiday blowout, X-Men style!
name: Hark How The Bells--!

first_appearance_locations.name: Jean Grey School for Higher Learning

location_credits.name: Jean Grey School for Higher Learning

description: "GOLGOTHA" Part 1 (of 5) A great big Marvel welcome to new writer Peter Milligan! The X-Men travel to Antarctica to respond to an S.O.S. from a colony of mutants…and what they find is far more shocking than they expected! Will the X-Men share the colony’s gruesome fate?
name: Golgotha, Part 1: And What Dark Beast...

description:
The Shape of Things to Come

First exciting issue! They were descendants of some of the greatest adventurers in literature from some of the great classics like Journey to Center of the Earth, 20,000 League Under the Sea, Mysterious Island, Invisible Man, Time Machine, Island of Dr. Moreau, and others. Now banded together, they champion the pursuit of knowledge, the marvels of scientific exploration, and the wonders of investigating the unknown in the world around us. The Searchers is an action adventure series that can be equally enjoyed by adolescents as well as adults.
name: Fiction Factory

description: The group, led by Professor Challenger, heads to the Arctic where they witness the death of one of their members as they race to find the secret which will unveil the past that eludes them. At death's door, they find what they're looking for...The Nautilus, formerly commanded by Captain Nemo.
name: Dream Harvesters

description: As the team takes over the Nautilus to carry on their mission, they find themselves attacked by a modern day submarine and they come face to face with their previously unknown nemesis. And what about the Time Traveler? What plans is he hatching?
name: Fragile Times

description: The epic battle between two of fiction's greatest characters, yet in this world they're part of the fabric of reality. An unexpected savior shows up and one of the members shows that evil traits, even in a fictional character, can be passed down from generation to generation. This conclusion leads into the next mini-series, Searchers: Apostles of Mercy.
name: Empire Day

description: After a year serving on board the Babylon 5 space station Jeffery Sinclair the commander of the station is recalled to earth and given a new assignment. Secrets about gaps in Sinclair's memory during the war with the Minbari are finally revealed to him by top Minbari leaders. The Minbari tell Sinclair that they believe he has a Minbari soul inside of him. Sinclair is finally offered a position as ambassador to Minbar. He accepts and we see him board a shuttle to begin his tenure as ambassador.
name: In Darkness Find Me
Treason
In Harm's Way
The Price Of Peace

description: Babylon 5 Pilot Warren Keffer with The Stations Chief of Security Micheal Garibaldi go investigate a planet hoping to find answers to the destruction of a base there. During the adventure Garibaldi tells Keffer about his first introduction to Jeffery Sinclair, the ships commander and Garibaldi's long time friend.
name: Shadows Past And Present, Part 1: With Friends Like These...

description:
Babylon 5 Security Chief Micheal Garibaldi accompanied by the stations young star fighter pilot Warren Keffer are attacked while they are investigating an alien outpost that has been destroyed. Garibaldi continues to recall the event surrounding his first meeting with Jeffery Sinclair and the alien encounter that is strikingly similar to the one Keffer and Garibaldi are in the midst of.
This issue is part 2 of 4 in the mini-series.
name: Shadows Past And Present, Part 2: Against The Odds

description:
Babylon 5 Security Chief Garibaldi continues to reflect about his past adventures with Jeffery Sinclair while he and B5 pilot Warren Keffer try to outrun the aliens that are pursuing them. After eventually running out of places to run, they hide in a small forest and temporarily elude their attackers. Keffer reaches his breaking point after arguing with Garibaldi in the woods and takes Garibaldi's weapon fom him and using it to threaten him. Garabaldi ducks several shots from Keffer, with a ricochet hitting a cloak alien thus breaking the spell it had over Keffer. The alien dissolves into samll particles after death making it impossible to examine.  Their hunt for answers continues. 

This issue is part 3 of 4 issues
name: Shadows Past And Present, Part 3: Survival The Hard Way

description: Babylon 5 chief of Security Garibaldi and the station's star fighter pilot continue on their adventure to find answers to the destruction of a alien base. Keffer and Garibaldi walk to a near by town while Garibaldi remenisis about the attack that he an the former commander of the station Jeffery Sinclair suffered that is strangely similar to the one he and Keffer currently face. Meanwhile Captain Sheridan and the rest of B5 attempt to contact the two men. Evntually Garibaldi and Keffer return to the station but are left with many questions about the attack by mysterious aliens and their connections to the Psi-corp group.
name: Shadows Past And Present, Part 5: Silent Enemies

description: Narn ambassador G'Kar kidnaps Babylon 5's chief of security Micheal Garibaldi during an attempt to make a hasty exit from the station. Command staff notice Garibaldi missing, and through a tip from one of G'Kar's fellow Narn inform them that he has most likely been taken by the ambassador and is being held hostage off the station. Garibaldi meanwhile attempts to break G'Kar down by singing rather annoying at him for the tenure of his imprisonment.
name: Laser-Mirror-Starweb, Part 1: Duet For Human and Narn in C Sharp
Laser-Mirror-Starweb, Part 2: Coda For Human and Narn in B Flat

description:
The Hangman stars in three reprint stories. "The Gallows and the Ghoul," "The Case of the Python's Curse" and "Pirates Out of the Past". Two Boy Buddies back-up stories.

Wilbur & Suzie also

Almost a complete Reprint of Top Notch Laugh Comics #45 by Archie/MLJ in 1944.

One text story, one 3-page comic story, the letters pages, and a promo ad have been omitted and replaced by ads. The cover is also entirely different.

Stories:

"But I hain't tempermental folks..." (6 pages) Pokey Oakey

"When Suzie finds a job..." (6 pages) Suzie

"What's your hurry Gus?" (6 pages) Gloomy Gus

Deep, Dark, Diplomatics (1 page, text)

"Dear readers, again we bring..." (6 pages) Dotty & Ditto

"Edgar Guest once said..." (6 pages) Twiddles

"Wilbur Wilkin has decided to join..." (6 pages) Wilbur Wilkin

The Ghost With the Fallen Arches (5 pages) Snoop McGook

"Can time be turned backwards?" (6 pages) Stupidman
reprints of various Archie/MLJ strips

What Makes a hero? Is it his actions, or is it the results of those actions? Powerless explores what it means to be a hero in very human terms. By re-imagining Marvel's most popular characters without superhuman powers, this series will strip down to the core heroes we have all come to know and love. These characters - including Peter Parker, Matt Murdock and Logan - were fated to be heroes. Just because Peter Parker wasn't bitten by a radioactive spider doesn't mean he didn't do battle with a madman named Norman Osborn. Matt Murdock? Blinded, yes - but with no heightened senses. However, he did become a legal champion of the poor in Hell's Kitchen, and he did cross paths with Wilson Fisk, the Kingpin. And Logan is, of course, the enigmatic - and amnesiac - drifter on the run from his past.

Peter Parker, Matt Murdock & Logan were fated to be heroes. If Peter Parker wasn't bitten by a radioactive spider would he still do battle with a madman named Norman Osborn? Matt Murdock, though blinded, had no heightened senses. Nevertheless, he became a legal champion of the poor in Hell's Kitchen, crossing paths with a powerful crime boss named Wilson Fisk -- the Kingpin. Logan, still an enigmatic, amnesiac drifter, is on the run from his bloody past, without mutant powers to save him. By re- imagining Marvel's most popular characters without superhuman powers, this series will strip these heroes to their core, exploring what it means to be a hero in very human terms.

Logan. Peter Parker. Matt Murdock. What If these icons were left powerless? Would their destinies change? Find out in this mind-blowing take from writers Matt Chernis and Peter Johnson and Alias artist Michael Gaydos. In this issue, Matt Murdock's life is about to take a turn for the worse, courtesy of the Kingpin.

With great power must come great responsibility… but when the entire Marvel Universe is recast as a world that is powerless… are our heroes still noble? Was it the radioactive spider bite that made Peter Parker a hero and Norman Osborn a villain? Or was it destiny?

Powerless nears its climactic conclusion as events surrounding Logan, Peter Parker, and Matt Murdock cause each of them to reach their breaking point. Logan finally gets his opportunity to get answers to the questions that have haunted him. Parker discovers that sometimes a person's actions can have disastrous unintended consequences, and Murdock tries to climb back from the abyss.

The mysteries of the Powerless universe are finally revealed in the series' climactic conclusion! What devastating truth will psychiatrist William Watts learn when the lives of Peter Parker, Matt Murdock and Logan all converge on him for the last time? In a world without powers, who will live and who will die? And who will be changed forever?

Things heat up as Spidey and the Black Cat face off against the might of the Sinister Twelve. HOLY COW, TRUE BELIEVERS! DID WE SAY TWELVE? Even with the tough-as-nails Black Cat by his side, how can the web-slinger possibly defeat twelve of the most powerful super-villains on the planet? You don’t want to miss this one, action fans!

Spider-man and Black-Cat are caught in an battle with the Green Goblin's new Sinister Twelve, and Mac Gargan aka the Scorpion has the venom symbiote and now is the new Venom. Plus a brainwashed Dr.Octopus is on the loose.
name: The Last Stand, Part 3

description:
The pulse-pounding conclusion to Mark Millar and Terry Dodson’s run on Marvel Knights Spider-Man, featuring a showdown for the ages! Spider-Man versus two of his biggest – and most popular--foes…with MJ’s life at stake!  
 
Spider-Man finds out green goblin took aunt may.He also finds out that Mary Jane has been kidnapped.It also seems like deja vu were he's taking her.And wait till you find out were Aunt May is hidden.Spider-Man also finds help from his feline friend Black Cat.And just when Spider-Man and Black Cat are cornered Captain America shows up with the avengers.And Doctor Octopus tries to kill Goblin all in this 1 action packed comic.
name: The Last Stand, Part 4

description: Green Arrow (Ollie), Green Arrow (Connor), and Speedy fight the Duke of Oil while Roy tries to get into the bank vault and save the people in the bank. Somewhere else someone is trying to contact Constantine Drakon.
name: New Business, Part 1; Southern Comfort

description: 72 hours before what is happening in Star City someone wants to hire Drakon to take out Green Arrow. Meanwhile Roy is trying to diffuse a bomb. Outside the bank they stop the Duke of Oil, but the Bank blows up... and Roy was inside.
name: New Business, Part 2; Greeks Bearing Gifts

description:
Retired 1950's super hero Comet returns to help Nova in his battle against Diamondhead!

Note: 1st appearance of Comet.
name: The Coming of the Comet

description: It's Metropolis mayhem in "Hero Hunters," Part 4! Chaos rides the dark alleys of Superman's city as the Birds hunt the unpredictable and extremely dangerous Thorn!
name: Hero Hunters, Part Four: She Rides the Eye of a Hurricane

description:
Surrounded by armed SHIELD troops, the X-Men choose to reason with Fury, explaining that they have discovered that Fury’s ally, Ord of the Breakworld, was experimenting on the resurrected Piotr Rasputin in order to create the cure. Questioned by Fury, Special Agent Brand, director of SHIELD’s extra-terrestrial directive-driven counterpart, SWORD, confirms.

Ord is from a planet called the Breakworld, which possesses technology to see glimpses of the future. In one glimpse, they saw that an Earth mutant – possibly an X-Man - destroys their planet in their lifetime. SWORD entered into an agreement with Ord and the Breakworld to create a cure for mutation – in lieu of an alien invasion. SWORD and Ord had enlisted the aid of Dr. Kavita Rao, using DNA from the Breakworld resuscitated Colossus to create it.

As Brand continues her explanation, rioting mutants, incensed by a possibility of a cure, break into Benetech, scattering the SHIELD agents. In the confusion, Ord sneaks away to his spacecraft. As he rockets away, with the cure formula, Colossus manages to launch Wolverine to the ship via a Fastball Special, and Wolverine manages to makes Ord land.

The situation diffused, Fury suggests they walk away and act like the incident never happened. Having no way to object, the X-Men comply. Back at the Institute, the X-Men take stock of their situation. The Beast is still torn by the cure, of which he possesses the last sample, though he will not take it – for now.

Taking a little private time, Kitty and Piotr ponder the meaning of finding each other again. Meanwhile, Emma and an unseen cohort ponder how, if at all, Colossus’ return changes their plan.
name: Gifted, Part 6

first_appearance_locations.name: Jean Grey School for Higher Learning

location_credits.name: Jean Grey School for Higher Learning

description: The X-Men race to the scene of a gigantic subterranean monster having emerged in Manhattan and begun a wave of destruction. Using their skills as best suits the situation, the X-Men save innocents, or telepathically compel them to move to safety, or use their powers to force the creature back into its hole. The team is soon joined by the Fantastic Four, who combine their powers with the X-Men, forcing the monster into the hole from which it emerged. Returning back to the mansion, the team is dismayed that their heroics played for less than thirty seconds on the news, while a star’s scandal garnered more than three minutes. As the group discusses whether they can ever get a fair shake with the media, one of the students, Hisako, arrives, worried about another missing student, Wing. She is joined by the Stepford Cuckoos and the telepathic Blindfold, who is only able to speak a cryptic warning. Elsewhere, in the Danger Room, Wing lies dead on the floor. Having been in a simulation of the ravine outside the school grounds, he tried to fly – despite having received “the Cure.” With his death, the simulation ends. Elsewhere, Special Agent Brand faces an inquiry into her recent action before a S.W.O.R.D. committee. Rather than apologetic, she states that she regrets nothing and would go to any means to safeguard the planet. She awaits their judgment.
name: Dangerous, Part 1

first_appearance_locations.name: Jean Grey School for Higher Learning

location_credits.name: Jean Grey School for Higher Learning

description:
Overview

Did you miss the return of Colossus last August? Were you the guy who said, "This book's never going to stay on schedule, so you waited for the trade paperback? Are you insane?! How can you wait!? Folks, if you're missing this, you're missing the best comic in comics right now (by someones opinion)! But, it's not too late to jump on board.

Just moments after Blindfold’s enigmatic warning, all of the telepaths and psychics in the Institute suffer a simultaneous attack, which knocks them out leaving them unable to reawaken. While the team moves them to the infirmary, miles away, a Sentinel which had been found by a local comes online, bursting forth from the barn where it had been kept. Lacking all limbs but its left arm, the Sentinel begins to drags itself toward the Institute… and its “Lord.” At the Institute, the X-Men are taking stock of their situation – the psychic attack and the still-missing student, Wing, and the inexplicable total communications blackout – when Lockheed arrives, warning them of an intrusion. When the X-Men go to investigate, they find the arriving Sentinel, who attacks both them and the school. Cyclops is able to eliminate its threat with a powerful optic blast and then order Wolverine to finish it off, while he and Colossus check on the students, whom he told Kitty to take to the Danger Room for safety. Wolverine makes short work but, before delivering the final blow, hears the unusually talkative Sentinel speak of its “Lord” and that the “children will pay for the father’s sins.” Racing back to the school, Wolverine finds that the other X-Men cannot gain entrance to the Danger Room and the children inside. As they theorize that their enemy is inside, Emma arrives with the Beast, explaining that the Danger Room itself is their enemy and that it is angry. Inside, the Danger Room has reanimated the corpse of Wing, shocking the rest of the students. Elsewhere, Special Agent Brand is awaiting the decision of the S.W.O.R.D. committee when she is visited by another agent, who informs here of the complete loss of all monitoring devices in the school.
name: Dangerous, Part 2

first_appearance_locations.name: Jean Grey School for Higher Learning

location_credits.name: Jean Grey School for Higher Learning

description:
A follow-up to the Eisner Award-winning FORMERLY KNOWN AS THE JUSTICE LEAGUE begins as the second story arc of this hot new series! The 6-part "I Can't Believe It's Not the Justice League"— written by Keith Giffen and J.M. DeMatteis with art and cover by Kevin Maguire and Joe Rubinstein — begins innocently enough with the newly established "Super Buddies" open for business — complete with their very own theme song. But things hit a sour note when a former foe opens a bar next door to their new "headquarters" in the strip mall downtown!

The Super Buddies have a new neighbour and Sue discovers that he use to be a super-villain by the name of Blackguard but appears to be the only one bothered about it. While Blue Beetle and Booster Gold exchange compliments on their new costumes, Fire is out looking for a new apartment she can share with their new team mate Mary Marvel who, in the process, is learning many things she really didn't need to. After Sue takes it upon her self to give their neighbour a warm welcome in the super-hero fashion, it's when the team see who Blackguard's partner is that they start to worry.
name: This Guy... This Gardner

story_arc_credits.name: I Can't Believe It's Not The Justice League

first_appearance_storyarcs.name: I Can't Believe It's Not The Justice League

description: A tale of revenge and honor told against the sun-bleached asphalt of the New West! Cinnamon's drifted for years as a hired gun along the Mexican border, but when a shady job takes her north, she must face up to the ghosts that haunt her dark past!
name: Inicio

description: The tale of revenge and honor in the New West continues! Modern-day gunslinger Cinnamon heads to L.A. to settle old business from the long-ago murder of her father. To get there, she'll make a deal with the devils dealing cheap immigrant labor to the City of Angels!
name: La  Demanda

description: The thrilling miniseries set in the New West continues! On the bad streets of South Cental L.A., a legendary tough girl comes face to face with the six-gun drifter who shot her father, Cinnamon.
name: Desfio

description: A south L.A. slum that's home to a family of runaways goes up in flames, revealing a big secret. That's when the modern-day gunslinger Cinnamon calls in her cavalry of showgirls, enforcers.and one extremely unlikely ally.
name: Fuego

description: The miniseries concludes with a bang! Cinnamon storms a Hollywood Hills estate side-by-side with her street-tough nemesis Mace Samuels to rescue the runaway that brought them together. Will this be the gunslinger's ticket out of L.A. ? or her tombstone?
name: Los Angeles

description: Her name is Sydney Taine, and by trade, she is a detective. But her investigations -- and her clients -- are far more dangerous than those of an ordinary private eye's. Her work takes her into the darkest corners of society -- to those places and beings that most people don't even know exist into the Nightside. She moves in a world of warring factions of supernatural creatures that call themselves "The Others." They appear to be human, but behind the facade lie thirsts, passions, and powers far beyond any normal human's. For you see, they've lived among us since before recorded history. Joining her is her partner Key "Ape" Largo, whose incredible intellect and heart are hidden in a massive body. Together, they stand between us and the forces of darkness that are concealed under the shade of night! In order to best bring this shadowy vision to life, artist Tom Derenick will be illustrating the series in gray tones. The result is a unique and disturbing experience in horror!

The supernatural series by award-winning horror writer Robert Weinberg continues! Detective Sydney Taine's investigation takes her deeper and deeper into the realm of The Others, a race that has existed clandestinely alongside humanity for thousands of years, but they're the least of Taine's problems! What is the Black Dragon Society? Why have they targeted certain rulers of the Other's underworld? And, what secret does Sydney herself conceal?

New York City's Nightside totters on the brink of all-out war as secret alliances and deadly betrayals are finally revealed! The only one with the power to end this ruthless game of cross and double-cross is supernatural detective, Sydney Taine. But she's caught in a killer-take-all battle with a near-invulnerable monster with ten times her strength!

Take a walk on the Nightside! A sword, a skull, and a seemingly innocent pair of spectacles. What incredible occult secret binds together the Three Lost Treasures of Tao? Can Sydney Taine, the mysterious female detective who dwells in the netherworld of vampires and werewolves known as the Nightside, defeat the demonic princess of the Black Dragons? It's cold steel vs. sizzling black magic as two very dangerous, very ambitious women collide in a battle that will at last reveal the truth about the darkness!

The EPIC imprint is launched with a story we couldn't tell in the Marvel Universe. Again at the forefront of telling stories for contemporary teens about the real issues they face, Mark Millar, Terry Dodson & Epic Comics present the story of four teenagers who spend a summer of love and romance, and then face consequences they will never forget … and neither will the comic book world!

"We really have to be as radical in our thinking here as Stan, Steve and Jack were back in the 60s. Just as Stan reinvented the superhero comic, Terry and I want to completely rewrite the book on what people might think of the ROMANCE comic. Yes, there's going to be plenty of very pretty and very horny people running around doing what comes natural, but I also want to add a level of sophistication to that sexuality, examine the consequences and produce a story that's going to have people talking for the next ten years. Marvel has always been the company that took the big risks, and this is their chance to make people outside our general market rethink their understanding of comic books all over again." - Mark Millar, February 2003
name: The Summer Everyone Lost It

description: Four teenagers learn their summer of carefree romance partying comes with life-changing consequences! Mark Millar and Terry & Rachel Dodson revive the romance comic in this funny, dramatic & thought-provoking tale of four young friends facing a crossroads! Featuring a surprise that will become the talk of the comic book world!
name: What Mom Never Told Us

description: Four young friends continue to deal with the consequences of their summer romances. For teenagers like May, Mary, Richard & Ben, sex can be very powerful, and as everyone knows, with great power comes great responsibility!

Overview                           

Ben, May, Mary & Richard continue to deal with the ramifications of their summer flings, including the one decision no teenage girl wants to face!

Overview                         

The conclusion of the shocking mini-series as a blessed event changes the lives of May, Ben, Richard and Mary forever!

Dr. Sun captures Nova to fulfill his plan of taking control of the Nova Prime ship. But is this really a cure for immortality? But Dr. Sun isn't the only one with Nova in his plans…

Nova and the Comet get thrashed by the nigh unstoppable Diamondhead. This leaves the Human Rocket vulnerable and at the mercy of Dracula's old nemesis Dr. Sun.
name: From the dregs of defeat!
